title.narrative: Ghar Ghar Ma Swasthya (GGMS)

description.narrative: (Nepal): USAID's Ghar Ghar Maa Swasthya (GGMS), or Healthy Homes Program, leverages social marketing initiatives and an extensive distribution network to enhance accessibility and availability of family planning and maternal and child health (MCH) products and services . To expand the market for these health products and thus promote the sustainability of MCH efforts, USAID will strengthen revenue generation in the existing market, implement behavior change communication through social marketing to improve nutritional practices for pregnant mothers and infant children, scale-up distribution of proven interventions such as oral rehydration therapy for diarrhea treatment, and provide technical assistance to private sector entities on quality assurance monitoring for HIV prevention among key high-transmission groups.
